        "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nUsing Lombok backfired, coverage actually dropped from 53.4% to 53.3% :-(",
        "patchset_number": 3
      },
      {
        "id": "7d2832488da5bbc8147aeb2617680d2e00040253",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 811,
          "name": "Jim Hahn",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "jrh3@att.com",
          "username": "jrh3"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2019-11-07 13:28:32.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\n> Using Lombok backfired, coverage actually dropped from 53.4% to\n > 53.3% :-(\n\nYeah.  Lombok reduces the denominator, which should make things look better, but I forgot that it may also reduce the numerator (e.g., when existing junits invoke \"get\" or \"set\" methods).  We could try changing the lombok.config to count coverage toward sonar - if it hurts things overall, we could revert it back.",
        "patchset_number": 3
      }
